{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"iddceee2c4-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s2281"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2281"},"text":"§ 2281.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Congressional findings and declaration of purpose","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Congress finds that demands for funds through Federal and federally assisted borrowing programs are increasing faster than the total supply of credit and that such borrowings are not adequately coordinated with overall Federal fiscal and debt management policies. The purpose of this chapter is to assure coordination of these programs with the overall economic and fiscal policies of the Government, to reduce the cost of Federal and federally assisted borrowings from the public, and to assure that such borrowings are financed in a manner least disruptive of private financial markets and institutions.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"iddceee2c5-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/224/s2"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–224, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-12-29"},"text":"Dec. 29, 1973","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/87/937"},"text":"87 Stat. 937","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"iddceee2c6-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"iddceee2c7-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDate","id":"iddceee2c8-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/224/s20"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–224, § 20","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-12-29"},"text":"Dec. 29, 1973","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/87/942"},"text":"87 Stat. 942","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/93/224/s20"},"text":"“This Act [enacting this chapter and amending ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s24"},"text":"section 24 of this title","children":[],"tail":"] becomes effective upon the date of its enactment ["},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-12-29"},"text":"Dec. 29, 1973","children":[],"tail":"], except that section 7 ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s2286"},"text":"section 2286 of this title","children":[],"tail":"] becomes effective upon the expiration of thirty days after such date ["},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-12-29"},"text":"Dec. 29, 1973","children":[],"tail":"].”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitle","id":"iddceee2c9-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/224/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–224, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-12-29"},"text":"Dec. 29, 1973","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/87/937"},"text":"87 Stat. 937","children":[],"tail":", provided: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/93/224/s1"},"text":"“That this Act [enacting this chapter and amending ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s24"},"text":"section 24 of this title","children":[],"tail":"] may be cited as the ‘Federal Financing Bank Act of 1973’.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"separability","id":"iddceee2ca-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Separability","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/224/s19"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–224, § 19","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-12-29"},"text":"Dec. 29, 1973","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/87/942"},"text":"87 Stat. 942","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/93/224/s19"},"text":"“If any provision of this Act [enacting this chapter and amending ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s24"},"text":"section 24 of this title","children":[],"tail":"], or the application thereof to any person or circumstance, is held invalid, the validity of the remainder of the Act [this chapter], and the application of such provisions to other persons or circumstances, shall not be affected.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"iddceee2cb-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Termination of Advisory Councils","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Advisory councils established after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-01-05"},"text":"Jan. 5, 1973","children":[],"tail":", to terminate not later than the expiration of the 2-year period beginning on the date of their establishment, unless, in the case of a council established by the President or an officer of the Federal Government, such council is renewed by appropriate action prior to the expiration of such 2-year period, or in the case of a council established by the Congress, its duration is otherwise provided for by law. See sections 1001(2) and 1013 of Title 5, Government Organization and Employees."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"execDoc","id":"iddceee2cc-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Executive Documents","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"executiveOrder","id":"iddceee2cd-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Executive Order No. 11782","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Ex. Ord. No. 11782, ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-05-06"},"text":"May 6, 1974","children":[],"tail":", 39 F.R. 15991, which established the Federal Financing Bank Advisory Council and provided for its membership, functions, etc., was revoked by Ex. Ord. No. 12379, § 15, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-08-17"},"text":"Aug. 17, 1982","children":[],"tail":", 47 F.R. 36099, formerly set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s1013"},"text":"section 1013 of Title 5","children":[],"tail":", Government Organization and Employees."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
